From tkeitt at utexas.edu  Tue Aug 11 18:06:24 2015
From: tkeitt at utexas.edu (Tim Keitt)
Date: Tue, 11 Aug 2015 11:06:24 -0500
Subject: [Rcpp-devel] Is Rcpp:: not a good choice for iterators?
In-Reply-To: <CAN55XP5C4KP+mwxiOATdiV9sj53N-GGm7ta-T7dC7N+68a9K1A@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAN55XP5C4KP+mwxiOATdiV9sj53N-GGm7ta-T7dC7N+68a9K1A@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <CANnL8gpz9nAVwEQbzD98e3OviHNozvCNpgnaeqPSnBTdJRKEQw@mail.gmail.com>

1) Figure out where you are making full copies of your data structures
(casting NumericVector to std::vector<double>)
2) Use eg R::rbinom instead of rbinom if you do not want the return as an
Rcpp Vector type.
3) Move the outer loop (your replicate call) into C++

The copying of data is what is slowing things down most likely.

T.

http://www.keittlab.org/

